# ========================================
# FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION
# ========================================

# API Base URL Configuration
# 
# OPTION 1: LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (Default)
# For running backend on your local machine (localhost)
# Backend should be running on http://localhost:5000
# UNCOMMENT the line below (it's the default if not set):
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000

# OPTION 2: PRODUCTION (Render)
# For connecting to the production/hosted backend on Render
# UNCOMMENT and use the line below:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://maty-shop.onrender.com

# NOTES:
# - If VITE_API_BASE_URL is not set, the app defaults to http://localhost:5000
# - The /api prefix is added automatically by the API service files
# - Make sure your backend is accessible at the URL you set
# - For local development: Start backend first on port 5000
#   Backend should be running on: http://localhost:5000
# ========================================
